US Homeland Security John Kelly said Sunday that he was considering banning laptop computers on international flights into and out of the country, amid signs of &#8220;a real threat.&#8221; Asked on Fox News whether he might implement such a wide-reaching ban, Kelly said, &#8220;I might.&#8221; He added: &#8220;There&#8217;s a real threat &#8212; numerous threats against aviation.&#8221; He said terrorists were &#8220;obsessed&#8221; with the idea of &#8220;knocking down an airplane in flight, particularly a US carrier.&#8221; Agence France-Presse For more news your way, follow The Citizen on Facebook and Twitter.